reviewText: The item came quickly as described. The content is great, as always with Peep and his friends. The show is educational without being boring, and the humor keeps us parents interested.

My 4 year old can watch this over and over (and so can I). Quack is our favorite and this DVD is perfect.
Episodes:
Soap Opera
Diva Duck
Peep's Moon Mission
The Many Moons of Quack the Duck
Finding Time
Smaller Than A Peep
Magic Duck Dance
Chirp Chirp Tweet Tweet Chirp
Peep never disappoints.  Period.  Great band of characters, intelligent subject matter, catchy theme song.  Give Peep a chance if you haven't.
I use these videos for inside recess... I was shocked that k-6th grade ALL enjoyed them  NOPE not a type  kindergarten THROUGH 6th grade laughed at these... and my 1 year old grandbaby lies them too

What can I say? Quack is awesome. Just wish they had all the Peep series available in one big collection! Every member of our family enjoys it from the 5 year old to the 9 year old to the 46 year old. When it went off Netflix, we were devestated. Glad to have finally discovered some DVDs.

All of the "Peep" DVDs are fantastic. Gentle humor that adults can enjoy while the kids are transfixed by the sweet adventures with a lovely science/joy of discovery edge. These are superior videos for children. The added bonus of Joan Cusack's narration for most of the series is icing on a very lovely cake.
